text: Kinistin 91 is an Indian reserve of the Kinistin Saulteaux Nation in Saskatchewan. It is 39 kilometers southeast of Melfort. In the 2016 Canadian Census, it recorded a population of 321 living in 82 of its 90 total private dwellings. In the same year, its Community Well-Being index was calculated at 46 of 100, compared to 58.4 for the average First Nations community and 77.5 for the average non-Indigenous community. ==References== Category:Indian reserves in Saskatchewan Category:Division No. 14, Saskatchewan
